The paper deals with secure distributed computation, which is a topic commonly studied in the cryptography (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. The use of polynomial codes to lower computational time is a technique often used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and the analysis of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the problem of matrix multiplication is a fundamental problem in computer science and is often studied in the context of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
